1
00:00:04,635 --> 00:00:06,735
Guru Mahārāj
will say,

2
00:00:06,735 --> 00:00:10,571
“Bhāgavatam takes it 
to another level,

3
00:00:10,571 --> 00:00:13,225
whereas, in Bhagavad-gītā 
you’re being told

4
00:00:13,225 --> 00:00:17,167
don’t quarrel with the environment, 
be tolerant.”

5
00:00:17,169 --> 00:00:19,615
The Śrīmad Bhāgavatam
is saying,

6
00:00:19,615 --> 00:00:22,481
[Krishna Consciousness | Not By Force]

7
00:00:22,481 --> 00:00:28,173
tat te ’nukampāṁ su-samīkṣamāṇo
bhuñjāna evātma-kṛtaṁ vipākam
[SB: 10.14.8]

8
00:00:28,173 --> 00:00:32,401
that su-samīkṣa—
if you scrutinize this,

9
00:00:32,401 --> 00:00:38,722
if you look deeply beneath the surface 
of karmic circumstance,

10
00:00:38,722 --> 00:00:41,843
and as we said—
acquired prejudice and tendencies—

11
00:00:41,843 --> 00:00:47,249
saṃskāra: one’s impressions lifetime
after lifetime, after lifetime …

12
00:00:47,433 --> 00:00:53,376
Acquired mental impressions,
layering, covering the self.

13
00:00:53,376 --> 00:00:57,275
If you look very deep
in your circumstances you’ll see,

14
00:00:57,275 --> 00:01:05,749
not only is toleration prescribed,
good prescription … but,

15
00:01:05,749 --> 00:01:09,787
in the background—
suhṛdaṁ sarva-bhūtānāṁ
[Bg: 5.29]

16
00:01:09,787 --> 00:01:12,786
the friendly hand of 
Kṛṣṇa is there.

17
00:01:12,786 --> 00:01:15,835
Who owns and
controls everything
 

18
00:01:15,835 --> 00:01:22,615
is not trying to crush you,
but, is your friend.

19
00:01:22,615 --> 00:01:32,291
And wanting to bring you 
out of karmic circumstance.

20
00:01:32,291 --> 00:01:36,638
So, what I mean to say here really,
to address the initial question,

21
00:01:36,638 --> 00:01:44,547
is that, that’s between God 
and that individual.

22
00:01:44,547 --> 00:01:53,727
We’re not to impose 
our conceptions upon others.

23
00:01:53,727 --> 00:01:57,831
If somebody sincerely inquires—
you try to answer as the best you can,

24
00:01:57,831 --> 00:02:03,241
but to try and change somebody
against their will,

25
00:02:03,241 --> 00:02:09,892
to try and impose, or enforce
some way of seeing on someone

26
00:02:09,895 --> 00:02:15,897
that is against … without their consent,
that they’re resistant to,

27
00:02:15,897 --> 00:02:21,518
that won’t be successful 
and it also begs the position

28
00:02:21,518 --> 00:02:27,556
of the person 
who’s the enforcer.

29
00:02:27,646 --> 00:02:34,271
But, in the case of,
you could say, devotees

30
00:02:34,271 --> 00:02:40,708
or say some devotee wife— 
she is concerned about her husband.

31
00:02:40,708 --> 00:02:51,792
Then the best thing 
is like we do for any new person

32
00:02:51,792 --> 00:02:55,314
is just give them exposure 
to Kṛṣṇa consciousness.

33
00:02:55,314 --> 00:02:57,255
Same thing parents do 
with their children,

34
00:02:57,255 --> 00:03:00,267
you give them exposure 
to Kṛṣṇa consciousness.

35
00:03:00,267 --> 00:03:06,472
How far they will embrace 
that is an individual thing.

36
00:03:06,491 --> 00:03:09,155
As we mention again 
in the Gītā,

37
00:03:09,155 --> 00:03:14,322
manuṣyāṇāṁ sahasreṣu
kaścid yatati siddhaye

38
00:03:14,322 --> 00:03:18,613
yatatām api siddhānāṁ
kaścin māṁ vetti tattvataḥ 
[Bg: 7.3]

39
00:03:18,613 --> 00:03:22,169
Kṛṣṇa Himself is saying 
in the Gītā again,

40
00:03:22,169 --> 00:03:25,461
and He should know—
He is situated in everyone’s heart.

41
00:03:25,461 --> 00:03:28,863
He can do His own 
demographic study,

42
00:03:28,863 --> 00:03:32,533
statistical analysis
at any given point and time.

43
00:03:32,533 --> 00:03:35,071
He is saying, 
“It’s very rare for someone
 

44
00:03:35,071 --> 00:03:41,843
to seriously express interest 
in spiritual culture,

45
00:03:41,843 --> 00:03:46,063
theistic culture, substantially. 
That’s rare.

46
00:03:46,063 --> 00:03:49,915
Out of thousands—one.”
And then what does He say?

47
00:03:49,919 --> 00:03:54,738
—And out of those 
who may become siddha

48
00:03:54,738 --> 00:03:57,038
in the general 
sense of the term—

49
00:03:57,038 --> 00:04:01,258
perfect, spiritually realized.
He says,

50
00:04:01,258 --> 00:04:05,287
kaścin māṁ vetti tattvataḥ
[Bg: 7.3]
 

51
00:04:05,287 --> 00:04:07,580
—Hardly one knows Me.
 

52
00:04:07,580 --> 00:04:10,230
Elsewhere, 
in the Bhāgavatam we hear, 
 

53
00:04:10,230 --> 00:04:14,649
muktānām api siddhānāṁ
nārāyaṇa-parāyaṇaḥ

54
00:04:14,649 --> 00:04:18,143
su-durlabhaḥ praśāntātmā
koṭiṣv api mahā-mune 
[SB: 6.14.5]

55
00:04:18,143 --> 00:04:22,161
—Out of ten million
liberated souls,

56
00:04:22,161 --> 00:04:25,788
one might be 
a devotee of Kṛṣṇa.

57
00:04:25,788 --> 00:04:29,098
And once Guru Mahārāj said,
“Even that is too many.”

58
00:04:29,098 --> 00:04:31,408
[Laughing]

59
00:04:31,428 --> 00:04:32,685
So what do we hear?

60
00:04:32,685 --> 00:04:36,236
koṭi-karma-niṣṭha-madhye eka ‘jñānī’ śreṣṭha
[Cc: 2.19.147]

61
00:04:36,282 --> 00:04:42,734
Out of ten million karmis … one jñānī
is better than ten million karmīs

62
00:04:42,734 --> 00:04:44,044
And then …

63
00:04:44,054 --> 00:04:50,273
koṭi-mukta-madhye
‘durlabha’ eka kṛṣṇa-bhakta
[Cc: 2.19.148]

64
00:04:50,273 --> 00:04:53,324
And out of millions
of liberated souls,

65
00:04:53,324 --> 00:04:56,931
one may be a devotee
of Kṛṣṇa.

66
00:04:56,931 --> 00:05:05,342
So it’s rare and generally
the outcome of accumulated sukriti,

67
00:05:05,352 --> 00:05:10,220
from ajñāta-sukṛti
to jñāta-sukṛti, śraddhā,

68
00:05:10,220 --> 00:05:11,564
sādhu-saṅga.

69
00:05:11,564 --> 00:05:16,203
So, Guru Mahārāj 
is telling us underground,

70
00:05:16,203 --> 00:05:19,260
ajñāta-sukṛti, 
which we define as

71
00:05:19,260 --> 00:05:26,731
some unknowing contact
with nirguṇa agents.

72
00:05:28,075 --> 00:05:38,897
So, if someone’s of a couple,
if one person is engaged

73
00:05:38,897 --> 00:05:41,597
in the culture of 
Kṛṣṇa consciousness,

74
00:05:41,597 --> 00:05:43,759
then by dent 
of connection with them,

75
00:05:43,759 --> 00:05:45,279
the other person
is going to get 
 

76
00:05:45,279 --> 00:05:48,242
a certain amount 
of exposure.

77
00:05:48,242 --> 00:05:55,729
And if they remain together
in a mutually, how we say,

78
00:05:55,729 --> 00:05:59,640
respectful relationship 
of one another,

79
00:05:59,640 --> 00:06:09,121
that person will accumulate
sukṛti, and in time it will …

80
00:06:10,551 --> 00:06:13,044
the accumulative effect
of that sukṛti

81
00:06:13,044 --> 00:06:18,886
will be expressed as śrāddha—
faith, which will lead them

82
00:06:18,886 --> 00:06:21,972
to take the association 
of devotees seriously.

83
00:06:22,212 --> 00:06:24,673
But as Gurudev 
would say in a phrase,

84
00:06:24,673 --> 00:06:30,265
you want to make it 
very simple, “Not to force.”

85
00:06:31,472 --> 00:06:37,105
Not to force with children, 
not to force with life partners.
 

